SIMPLE: magnify
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magnify
<hw>Mag"ni*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Magnified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Magnifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>magnifien</ets>, F. <ets>magnifier</ets>, L.
<ets>magnificare</ets>. See <er>Magnific</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To make great, or greater; to increase the dimensions of; to
amplify; to enlarge, either in fact or in appearance; <as>as, the
microscope <ex>magnifies</ex> the object by a thousand
diameters</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The least error in a small quantity . . . will in a great one . .
. be proportionately <qex>magnified</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Grew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To increase the importance of; to augment the esteem
or respect in which one is held.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On that day the Lord <qex>magnified</qex> Joshua in the sight of
all Israel.</q> <rj><qau>Joshua iv. 14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To praise highly; to laud; to extol.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, <qex>magnify</qex> the Lord with me, and let us exalt his name
together.</q> <rj><qau>Ps. xxxiv. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To exaggerate; <as>as, to <ex>magnify</ex> a loss or
a difficulty</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To magnify one's self</b></col> <fld>(Script.)</fld>,
<cd>to exhibit pride and haughtiness; to boast.</cd> -- <col><b>To
magnify one's self against</b></col> <fld>(Script.)</fld>, <cd>to oppose
with pride.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magnify</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Magnify
<hw>Mag"ni*fy</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To have the power
of causing objects to appear larger than they really are; to increase
the apparent dimensions of objects; <as>as, some lenses <ex>magnify</ex>
but little</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To have effect; to be of importance or
significance.</def> <mark>[Cant & Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spectator.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>magnifying glass</ent>⟦br⟧
